nclude atrioventricular block, ventricular arrhythmias, cardiac arrest, and decreased cardiac output and arterial blood pressure due to depressed cardiac conductivity, excitability, and myocardial contractility.  Patients should have cardiovascular and respiratory vital signs and state of consciousness constantly monitored while under treatment.', 'Others', 'Chloroprocaine, Tetracaine, Mepivacaine, Meloxicam, Procaine, Prilocaine, Articaine, Etidocaine', 'Quinidine, Amiodarone, Dronedarone, Propafenone, Tocainide, Procainamide, Flecainide, Disopyramide, Dofetilide, Bretylium, Moricizine, Ibutilide', 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/260780/', '[1] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[2] "Product Information. Exparel (BUPivacaine liposome)." Pacira Pharmaceuticals Inc  (2011):[3] Kharitonov V "A review of the compatibility of liposome bupivacaine with other drug products and commonly used implant materials." Postgrad Med 126 (2014):  129-38', 1767369485);
